article.headline: Ohio 66, Akron 63
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Leon Williams and Jeremy Fears both hit a pair of free throws in the final 10 seconds to push Ohio past Akron 66-63 on Tuesday night. The Bobcats held the Zips without a field goal over the final 2:22 and outscored the Zips 32-22 in the paint. Williams led Ohio (12-3, 6-1 Mid-American) with 16 points and 10 rebounds. Jerome Tillman had 11 points off the bench, and Mychal Green and Johnnie Jackson each added 10. Romeo Travis led Akron (13-4, 6-1) with 17 points. Dru Joyce scored 11 and Nate Linhart added 10. The Bobcats held Akron to 33 percent shooting in the second half and never trailed after Fears' jumper gave them a 34-33 halftime lead. The Zips scored the game's first 10 points and led 21-11 with 9:03 left in the first half. The Bobcats went on a 9-0 run and grabbed a 32-31 lead with 1:39 left in the half.
